com.github.dm.jrt.stream

Class AbstractStreamChannel<OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.dm.jrt.stream.AbstractStreamChannel<OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    OUT - the output data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConfigurableBuilder<StreamChannel<OUT>>, Channel, Channel.OutputChannel<OUT>, InvocationConfiguration.Configurable<StreamChannel<OUT>>, StreamChannel<OUT>, Iterable<OUT>, Iterator<OUT>

    public abstract class AbstractStreamChannel<OUT>
extends Object
implements StreamChannel<OUT>, InvocationConfiguration.Configurable<StreamChannel<OUT>>
    Abstract implementation of a stream output channel.

    This class provides a default implementation of all the stream channel features. The inheriting class just needs to create routine and channel instances when required.

    Created by davide-maestroni on 01/12/2016.

      • backPressureOn

        @NotNull
public StreamChannel<OUT> backPressureOn(@Nullable
                                        Runner runner,
                                        int maxInputs,
                                        long maxDelay,
                                        @NotNull
                                        TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Description copied from interface: StreamChannel
        Short for invocationConfiguration().withRunner(runner).withInputLimit(maxInputs) .withInputMaxDelay(maxDelay, timeUnit).setConfiguration().
        This method is useful to easily apply a configuration which will slow down the thread feeding the next routine concatenated to the stream, when the number of buffered inputs exceeds the specified limit. Since waiting on the same runner thread is not allowed, it is advisable to employ a runner instance different from the feeding one, so to avoid deadlock exceptions.
        Specified by:
        backPressureOn in interface StreamChannel<OUT>
        Parameters:
        runner - the configured runner.
        maxInputs - the maximum number of buffered inputs before starting to slow down the feeding thread.
        maxDelay - the maximum delay to apply to the feeding thread.
        timeUnit - the delay time unit.
        Returns:
        the configured stream.

                                BiFunction<? super OUT,? super OUT,? extends OUT> function)
        Description copied from interface: StreamChannel
        Concatenates a stream based on the specified accumulating function to this one.
        The output will be computed as follows, where the initial accumulated value will be the the first input: 
             

         acc = function.apply(acc, input);
        The accumulated value will be passed as result only when the outputs complete.

        Description copied from interface: StreamChannel
        Concatenates a stream generating the output returned by the specified iterable.
        The outputs will be generated only when the previous routine invocations complete.

        Note that the created routine will be initialized with the current configuration.
        Note also that this stream will be bound as a result of the call.
